 in another organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of acid-sensing ion channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of ASIC channel activity in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated inhibition of acid-sensing ion channel activity\" RELATED []\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0160128 ! pH-gated monoatomic ion channel activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29375\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29859\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-11-06T16:05:58Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044741\nname: venom-mediated suppression of sensory perception of pain\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts sensory perception of pain in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:23034652]\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in inhibition of sensory perception of pain in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of sensory perception of pain in another organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in negative regulation of sensory perception of pain in other organism\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0019233 ! sensory perception of pain\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29375\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-11-07T14:02:14Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044742\nname: venom-mediated increase of sensory perception of pain\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances sensory perception of pain in another organism via the action of a venom. Can manifest as allodynia, a condition that causes pain when a stimulus that normally wouldn't cause pain, or hyperalgesia, an increased sensitivity to feeling pain and an extreme response to pain.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:23034652]\nsynonym: \"allodynia\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"hyperalgesia\" NARROW []\nis_a: GO:0140136 ! venom-mediated perturbation of nervous system process\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0019233 ! sensory perception of pain\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29375\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-11-07T14:26:38Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140099\nname: venom-mediated suppression of fibrinolysis\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts fibrinolysis in another organism via the action of a venom. Fibrinolysis is the solubilization of fibrin in the bloodstream. Anti-fibrinolytic proteins reduce bleeding at the bite or sting site of the prey.\" [PMID:19236611, PMID:22359676, PMID:27208884, PMID:35716829]\nsynonym: \"envenomation suppressing fibrinolysis in another organism\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nintersection_of: GO:0044483 ! venom-mediated perturbation of hemostasis\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0042730 ! fibrinolysis\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29652\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29851\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-02-04T15:52:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140134\nname: venom-mediated perturbation of blood circulation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts the circulation of blood in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:31370142]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated perturbation of cardiovascular system\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated perturbation of circulatory system process\" BROAD []\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0008015 ! blood circulation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29794\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30014\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-02-25T09:17:46Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140136\nname: venom-mediated perturbation of nervous system process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts a nervous system process in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:pg]\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0050877 ! nervous system process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29794\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-02-25T09:18:10Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140137\nname: venom-mediated perturbation of muscle system process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts a muscular process in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [GOC:pg]\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0003012 ! muscle system process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29794\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-02-25T09:18:30Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140138\nname: venom-mediated disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of an anatomical structure in another organism via the action of a venom. Venoms are injected into the prey by a bite or a sting.\" [GOC:pg]\nis_a: GO:0141060 ! disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29794\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-02-25T09:31:25Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140162\nname: venom-mediated vasodilation by activation of bradykinin receptor signaling pathway\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances vasodilation via the action of a venom that activates bradykinin-dependent signaling, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism. This can take place via several mechanisms that affect endogenous bradykinin: either increasing its release by kallikrein-like proteases, increasing bradykinin action by potentiation, or inhibiting bradykinin degradation.\" [PMID:31370142]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation by activation of bradykinin-dependent signaling\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation through activity of bradykinin\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044513 ! venom-mediated perturbation of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway\nis_a: GO:0044551 ! venom-mediated vasodilation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30014\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-04-01T09:16:39Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140163\nname: venom-mediated suppression of bradykinin-dependent vasodilation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts vasodilation via the action of a venom that suppresses bradykinin-dependent signaling.\" [PMID:21889567, PMID:31370142]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via bradykinin receptor antagonism\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0044513 ! venom-mediated perturbation of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway\nis_a: GO:0140134 ! venom-mediated perturbation of blood circulation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30014\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30211\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-04-01T09:29:25Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140165\nname: venom-mediated vasodilation by activation of nitric oxide-cGMP-mediated signaling\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances vasodilation via the action of a venom that activates nitric oxide-cGMP-mediated signaling, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:10512636]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation induced by nitric oxide activity\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044551 ! venom-mediated vasodilation\nrelationship: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0038060 ! nitric oxide-cGMP-mediated signaling\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30014\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-04-01T09:40:15Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140166\nname: venom-mediated vasodilation via suppression of angiotensin maturation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances vasodilation via the action of a venom that prevents angiotensin maturation, concomittantly reducing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:31370142]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation mediated by inhibition of angiotensin-converting enzyme\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasodilation through perturbation of angiotensin maturation\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044509 ! venom-mediated perturbation of signal transduction\nis_a: GO:0044551 ! venom-mediated vasodilation\nrelationship: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0002003 ! angiotensin maturation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30014\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-04-01T09:46:06Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140183\nname: venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin receptor signaling pathway\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism promotes the narrowing (constriction) of blood vessels, by inhibiting the widening (dilation) of blood vessels in another organism via the action of a venom that activates endothelin receptor signaling pathway, concomittantly increasing blood pressure in the bitten/stung organism.\" [PMID:16277978]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin signaling pathway\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via activation of endothelin-dependent signaling\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated vasoconstriction via endothelin receptor agonism\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0086100 ! endothelin receptor signaling pathway\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30211\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-06-26T08:05:09Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140184\nname: venom-mediated suppression of blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism inhibits or disrupts blood coagulation in another organism by suppression of the intrinsic pathway via the action of a venom. A common mechanism is the blocking the activity of host coagulation Factor XIIa (F12).\" [PMID:25724270]\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated suppression of blood coagulation cascade, contact activation system\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007597 ! blood coagulation, intrinsic pathway\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30519\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-06-27T13:34:32Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140342\nname: venom-mediated perturbation of heart contraction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which an organism alters or subverts the heart contractility in another organism via the action of a venom.\" [PMID:38167790]\nintersection_of: GO:0035738 ! venom-mediated perturbation of biological process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0060047 ! heart contraction\nrelationship: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0008015 ! blood circulation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31096\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2025-11-20T10:56:34Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140548\nname: obsolete venom-mediated platelet agglutination\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process in which an organism initiates, promotes, or enhances platelet agglutination in another organism via the action of a venom. This may takes place is via specific proteins binding to cell-surface carbohydrates on the platelet's cell membrane, resulting in calcium-dependent agglutination.\" [PMID:10484740, PMID:28435120]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as venom-mediated platelet aggregation ; GO:0044478.\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in blood agglutination in another organism\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"envenomation resulting in blood agglutination in other organism\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"venom-mediated blood agglutination\" BROAD []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18979\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0044478\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2020-11-11T21:42:31Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141123\nname: venom-mediated dermonecrosis in another organism\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The disruption of the skin of another organism, leading to damage or temporary subversion of the skin.\" [PMID:28194160]\nis_a: GO:0140138 ! venom-mediated disruption of anatomical structure in another organism\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26513\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-12-01T15:13:15Z\n\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
