{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' references_cache/PMID_19000915.md\"","aggregated_output":"---\nreference_id: PMID:19000915\ntitle: \"BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\"\nauthors:\n- Gomes MS\n- Mendes MM\n- de Oliveira F\n- de Andrade RM\n- Bernardes CP\n- Hamaguchi A\n- de Alcântara TM\n- Soares AM\n- Rodrigues VM\n- Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\njournal: Toxicon\nyear: '2009'\ndoi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Bothrops/physiology\n- Crotalid Venoms/enzymology\n- \"Dose-Response Relationship, Drug\"\n- Edema/chemically induced\n- Hemorrhage/chemically induced\n- Hindlimb\n- Male\n- \"Metalloproteases/chemistry, metabolism\"\n- Mice\n- \"Muscle, Skeletal/drug effects, pathology\"\ncontent_type: abstract_only\n---\n\n# BthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake venom.\n**Authors:** Gomes MS, Mendes MM, de Oliveira F, de Andrade RM, Bernardes CP, Hamaguchi A, de Alcântara TM, Soares AM, Rodrigues VM, Homsi-Brandeburgo MI\n**Journal:** Toxicon (2009)\n**DOI:** [10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007)\n\n## Content\n\n1. Toxicon. 2009 Jan;53(1):24-32. doi: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007. Epub 2008\nOct  17.\n\nBthMP: a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase from Bothrops moojeni snake \nvenom.\n\nGomes MS(1), Mendes MM, de Oliveira F, de Andrade RM, Bernardes CP, Hamaguchi A, \nde Alcântara TM, Soares AM, Rodrigues VM, Homsi-Brandeburgo MI.\n\nAuthor information:\n(1)Instituto de Genética e Bioquímica, Universidade Federal de Uberlândia (UFU), \n38400-902 Uberlândia-MG, Brazil. mrochauesb@yahoo.com.br\n\nIn this work, a new weakly hemorrhagic metalloproteinase (BthMP) was purified \nfrom Bothrops moojeni snake venom. This enzyme was homogeneous by native and \nSDS-PAGE. It showed a polypeptide chain of 23.5kDa, pI=7.1, and N-terminal \nblocked. BthMP is comprised of high proteolytic activity on casein, fibrin and \nbovine fibrinogen, with no coagulating, esterase or phospholipase A(2) \nactivities; it was inhibited by EDTA, EGTA and 1,10-phenanthroline and \nmaintained its activity on pH from 7.0 to 9.0 and temperature from 5-40 degrees \nC. Assays with metal ions showed that Ca(2+) is an activator, whereas Zn(2+) and \nHg(2+) inhibited about 50 and 80% of its activity, respectively. The edema \nevidenced the important role of the toxin in the inflammatory activity of the \nvenom. BthMP also caused unclotting, and provoked histological alterations in \nthe gastrocnemius muscle of mice inducing hemorrhage, necrosis and leukocytic \ninfiltrate. The molecular mass and the inhibition assays suggest that the \nmetalloproteinase BthMP belongs to class P-I of SVMPs.\n\nDOI: 10.1016/j.toxicon.2008.10.007\nPMID: 19000915 [Indexed for MEDLINE]","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
